### FE UX Plan (Tokens, A11y, Perf Budgets)

- Goal(s): Establish tokens, accessibility, and performance budgets (LCP/INP/CLS).

### Assumptions
- Design system tokens exported to code; AA contrast minimum.

### Alternatives
- Local component styles (inconsistent); skip perf budgets (risk).

### Risks & Mitigations
- Token drift (M×M): Token pipeline; visual regression tests.
- A11y gaps (M×H): ARIA reviews; keyboard traps tests.

### Dependencies
- Design tokens pipeline; Storybook; Lighthouse/ Web Vitals.

### Tokens
- Core: color, spacing, typography, radius, elevation
- Semantic: brand, states, feedback
- Export: platform-agnostic JSON → platform build

### Perf Budgets
- LCP ≤ 2.5s (p75), INP ≤ 200ms (p75), CLS ≤ 0.1 (p75)
- Bundle budget per route; image policy; font loading strategy

### Trigger → Rule → File(s)/Output mapping

| Trigger | Rules | Files/Outputs | Gates |
|---|---|---|---|
| foundation, tokens | `common-ui-foundation-design-system` | This plan | Token build passes |
| a11y, LCP/INP/CLS | `common-ui-interaction-a11y-perf` | Storybook a11y/perf reports | WCAG AA, Web Vitals checks |
| premium/enterprise | `common-ui-premium-brand-dataviz-enterprise-gated` | Brand guidelines | AA guarded visuals |

### Success Metrics
- ≥95 Lighthouse a11y; budgets enforced in CI.

### Next Steps
- Author tokens; wire a11y/perf checks in CI and Storybook.
